    "synopsis": "Two paired stories of the Knights Errant programme. In Ghosts Speak Not, Nathaniel Garro stands in for a Sigillite who will not appear in person and carries a new task to Amendera Kendel, once a Sister of Silence and now one of Malcador's quiet hands. Patience turns to the seventy loyal sons of the Death Guard that Garro carried away from Isstvan aboard the Eisenstein — a brotherhood that has spent the war so far penned on Luna, distrusted by both sides, and that is about to be given a purpose again under Helig Gallor's command. Together the two pieces sketch the moment a half-secret order of agents starts gathering its long-overlooked survivors and pointing them at the war that still has need of them.",
